# Contributor workflow

See [README.md](README.md) and the
[Consensys documentation contribution guidelines](https://docs-template.consensys.net/)
for baseline workflow.

## Sidebars

Sidebars are configured in `sidebars.js`.
Most sections are autogenerated from filesystem structure.

Use `_category_.json`, `sidebar_position`, and `sidebar_label` to control ordering and labels.

## Redirects

Every deleted, renamed, or moved page should have redirect coverage:

- Add or update redirect entries in `docusaurus.config.js` under `@docusaurus/plugin-client-redirects`.
- Update `vercel.json` when versioned route behavior also needs adjustment.

Broken links fail builds (`onBrokenLinks: "throw"`).

## Factual accuracy

Do not invent CLI flags, REST API fields, defaults, or operational behavior.
If uncertain, flag the uncertainty for review.

## Issue intake

Issue templates live in `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`.
When issue context is sparse, verify behavior from source materials before updating docs.

## Images

Store doc images in `static/img/` and link them with site paths (for example, `/img/<file-name>`).

## Keep rule files current

If you change documentation structure, naming, or formatting conventions, update the matching
`.cursor/rules/` file in the same PR so AI guidance does not go stale.

## CI linting and verification

Before requesting review:

- Run local preview with `npm start`.
- Run lint checks used by CI.
- Verify redirects and links.

CI includes docs linting, markdown linting, link checks, and builds.
